        <title>Create Action Items (required for administrators)</title>
        <contents>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Create one action item for each of the following:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;How will you give teachers the time and space for embedding more practice in academic language into curricula in your program (e.g., study circles, peer observations)?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Choose appropriate tools: Which tools or materials in this unit will you use or direct teachers to in your program?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Provide feedback: As you observe or mentor teachers, what could you do differently to provide feedback in the area of academic language?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-left: 30px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Share your responses to this activity in your&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Community of Practice, or with your colleagues on the &lt;a href="https://community.lincs.ed.gov/comment/16537#comment-16537" title="ESL Pro Module 1 Unit 2 Discussion Forum"&gt;LINCS discussion forum&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
